Game code: 1.37.0
Safe Hand of the King strategy: My goal is getting to Hand of the King as fast as possible! Before start choose TARGARYEN as your house. This might surprise you but let me explain. 1: You do not have to play that house! 2. You will have both GREYJOY and LANNISTER lit when starting multiball. 3. If you feel like you won't finish the modes within the allotted time you can hit button for 20s freeze timers! This is very important since you really want both modes completed when multiball is over.
If for some reason the houses are still alive I usually go for left loop and collecting lanes up top until Battle for the Wall multiball is lit. Then start the unfinished mode(s) again and start Battle for the Wall as quickly as you can at the dragon.
After multiball 3 houses should now be complete. Simply go for STARK ramp 3 times to light the mode and start it as soon as possible. If you feel confident about the middle ramp you can go for more than the 3 needed. Keep in mind that the points without multiplier is not worth going for. It's way more important to complete STARK to light Hand of the King.
When Hand of the King completes you should start working on your second regular multiball. You have to shoot both green targets which also advances towards TYRELL!
Also light BARATHEON or/and MARTELL as you need to finish these modes as well. Preferably during a multiball for safety. If you have your button special available, USE IT! Iron Throne has no timer and the mode is very long so you might lose your ball and waste your button.
When all houses has been beaten you challenge the Iron Throne. It's not very often you get to this point during tournament play but if you do: enjoy it!
